    "source_note": "No ADI specified - considered safe for use at quantum satis levels. SSL is one of the key ingredients that allows commercial bread to stay soft for days or weeks, whereas homemade bread without SSL typically goes stale within 1-2 days. It's found in nearly all commercial bread products."
